- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses category theory, which is a branch of mathematics closely related to logic, to provide a unifying approach to the study of many-one reductions. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper discusses degree structures arising from many-one reductions, which is a topic that falls under the scope of discrete mathematics. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper mentions the relevance of many-one reductions in algorithmic game theory, which is a subfield of computer science that studies the interaction between algorithms and game theory. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper mentions the concept of wtt-degrees, which is related to the theory of information and communication.
